description:
Recently sold: $242,000. Homeowner Contact: Erik 651-315-1081

Move in ready. Great corner lot. 3 season porch and new deck off back. Master suite with tiled full bath, fresh paint and newer carpet in basement and 2nd floor. Lower level theater room. Roof is 7 years old.

Massive 4-car Garage, Literally as big as the city would allow. This garage is loaded and ready to go.

-Epoxy Coated Floors
-80k BTU Natural Gas Heater
-Seperate Wi-fi network
-Plenty of 120v outlets and (2) 220v receptacles
-Fully Insulated walls and Ceiling
-(2) Ceiling Fans and (2) Exhaust fans for odor control

Basement has been re-done with (10) LED dimmable recessed lights. We will also be leaving the home theatre set-up, which includes:

-Optoma 3D projector
-120" Screen
-Pioneer 7.1 Surround Sound with ceiling-mounted speakers
-Stereo Receiver with 2 HDMI inputs

You haven't lived until you've seen 'Twister' on a 10 ft screen in your basement, Video games are awesome on this thing as well. Bring your Xbox or PS4 and enjoy literally plug and play, It's all ready to go.

On the other side of the basement is a Full-size fridge, Microwave and an 8 foot long, Slate-Faced bar. Lets just say the super bowl party is always at my house.

On the other side of the basement is the Laundry room, with Epoxy Coated floors this is a durable and easy to clean room with plenty of lighting and easy access to all the appliances and utilities.

-Water Heater replaced Dec 2017
-Complete Furnace and A/C unit replaced May 2006
-Washer and Gas Dryer are about 6 years old and work great
-Home is set-up with a Culligan water softener that is a rented unit
-There is also a large Deep Freeze that will be staying with the home

Kitchen with Electric Stove, Microwave and Fridge. Plenty of storage in the cabinets and the included hutch that matches the kitchen table.

Dining room has plenty of light and the hardwood floors make for easy clean-up.

Living room is an impressive 12x20 with south facing windows for natural light and has tons of outlets and is wired for cable/internet

Bedroom #1 on 1st floor has 2 closets with doors to keep the clutter away

bedroom #2 on 1st floor is a 9x10 with a 8-ft long closet with hanger rack and shelf, this has been a perfect guest bedroom with the pull-out day bed.

1st floor bath has nice tile with a large linen cabinet


onto the 2nd floor, This would be considered the master suite. Large, Open bedroom with a large full-bathroom with newer tile work. There is a closet at the top of the stairs and (4) attic access doors for storage. There is also a large dormer that could be opened up for a walk-in closet with a couple weekends of work.

This house is move-in ready and has tons of room for all your toys.

Recently sold: $300,000. Attached heated Garage, CCTV exterior Cameras, Interior/Exterior Intercom system, 2 city lots. 4 Bedrooms on 2nd Floor, with separate office. Main floor has formal living, plus den area. Basement includes it's own kitchenette area, with additional living room, bedroom and full bath.

description:
Recently sold: $201,000. This charming 1950s home has been lovingly cared for by the family who owns it. The yard has been completely redone to include several low-maintenance perennial gardens in the front and back yards, along with a pair of plumb trees that flower in the spring.

In 2014, new kitchen flooring was installed and a breakfast nook with bay window was added to the kitchen. In 2016, the backyard fence was replaced and a new window was added to the living room on the main level. In 2017, a drop ceiling was added to the laundry room and the original garage siding was replaced with vinyl siding.
